claim.claim-text:
13. The computer system of claim 10 wherein said computer system is programmed to:
compare the card identifier within the authorization request message to data stored in the storage device;
identify the transaction as involving the enhanced payment card based on the comparison of the card identifier with the stored data;
add a product code to the authorization request message, the product code indicating that the transaction is associated with the enhanced payment card; and
transmit the authorization request message with the product code to the issuer.

19. The least one computer-readable storage media of claim 16, wherein the computer-executable instructions further cause the at least one processor to:
compare the card identifier within the authorization request message to data stored in a storage device;
identify the transaction as involving the enhanced payment card based on the comparison of the card identifier with the stored data;
add a product code to the authorization request message, the product code indicating that the transaction is associated with the enhanced payment card;
transmit the authorization request message with the product code to the issuer;
transmit an authorization response message including the product code to the merchant; and
receive a clearing message including the addendum file from the merchant, wherein the addendum file is created based on the product code.
